00:00:04.141 --> 00:00:08.926
Namaste, I'm Lata Jain,
Welcome to Lata's Kitchen

00:00:08.926 --> 00:00:16.016
Puri is a very popular north Indian
bread prepared on special occasions

00:00:16.016 --> 00:00:23.555
Urad dal puri tastes very delicious, today
I'm going to make Mixed Urad Dal Puri

00:00:23.555 --> 00:00:28.125
Lets see the ingredients
required for making this

00:00:28.125 --> 00:00:36.374
For this we'll need

00:00:37.266 --> 00:00:39.609
Whole Wheat Flour - 1 1/2 cup

00:00:39.760 --> 00:00:50.547
Washed Urad Dal - 1/2 cup, washed and
soaked for 6 hour in 8 times water

00:00:50.547 --> 00:00:53.358
Garam Masala - 1/4 tsp

00:00:53.408 --> 00:00:56.598
Coriander Powder - 2 tsp

00:00:56.598 --> 00:01:00.596
Red Chilly Powder - 1/2 tsp

00:01:00.596 --> 00:01:03.061
Asafoetida - 2 pinch

00:01:03.061 --> 00:01:06.273
Salt - 1 tsp

00:01:06.273 --> 00:01:09.297
Fennel Seeds - 1 tsp

00:01:09.347 --> 00:01:11.800
Oil - 3 tbsp

00:01:11.800 --> 00:01:13.461
Water for kneading dough

00:01:13.461 --> 00:01:16.046
Oil for frying

00:01:16.046 --> 00:01:20.219
Lets start making puri

00:01:21.508 --> 00:01:38.930
Make a smooth paste of dal using a blender

00:01:39.984 --> 00:01:42.211
Add a little water

00:01:43.969 --> 00:01:49.313
Dal paste is ready, now add all the spices

00:02:02.445 --> 00:02:05.180
Now add whole wheat flour

00:02:11.313 --> 00:02:14.984
Mix well

00:02:17.835 --> 00:02:29.472
Make a hard dough of this
by adding little water at a time

00:02:33.070 --> 00:02:40.133
Dough is ready, now cover it
and let it rest for 10 minutes

00:02:44.203 --> 00:02:48.404
Its been 10 minutes, now check the dough

00:02:50.023 --> 00:02:52.875
Dough is ready

00:02:57.016 --> 00:03:00.677
Grease hands with some oil

00:03:06.938 --> 00:03:16.234
Make lemon size balls of this dough

00:03:17.445 --> 00:03:22.797
Now smooth these balls with your palm

00:03:25.617 --> 00:03:40.891
Similarly make all the balls and cover them

00:03:41.672 --> 00:03:47.470
All the balls are ready,
it makes around 30 balls

00:03:49.627 --> 00:03:56.093
Now heat the oil in a wok / kadhai

00:03:58.313 --> 00:04:09.359
check the heat by adding a tiny ball
of dough, it it floats oil is ready

00:04:10.344 --> 00:04:19.043
Grease the rolling board
and roller with some oil

00:04:21.008 --> 00:04:28.252
Place the ball in the
center of rolling board

00:04:28.278 --> 00:04:35.955
Now roll it into a circle of
about 3 inch light handedly

00:04:36.437 --> 00:04:40.116
It should neither be too thick nor too thin

00:04:40.461 --> 00:04:46.781
Turn gas to high, and place
the puri into the oil

00:04:48.039 --> 00:04:51.164
Press it with a skimmer

00:04:51.984 --> 00:04:57.375
It is puffed, now take it out from
the oil and place it on a plate

00:05:14.289 --> 00:05:16.118
Turn heat to high

00:05:16.828 --> 00:05:19.211
Place puri in the oil

00:05:31.555 --> 00:05:34.752
It is puffed, take it out
and place on a plate

00:05:35.461 --> 00:05:38.820
Similarly roll and fry about 3-4 puri

00:05:39.133 --> 00:05:47.297
Now put the previous single
side fried puri into the oil

00:05:52.844 --> 00:05:58.881
Fry from both the sides until golden brown

00:06:00.070 --> 00:06:09.445
Dal mixture will be cooked
properly by frying it two times

00:06:12.023 --> 00:06:16.927
Urad dal can also be stuffed instead
of mixing with dough, for this you

00:06:16.953 --> 00:06:21.924
can watch my recipe video 
"Kachori / Bedmi ( Urad Dal Stuffed Puri ) "

00:06:22.258 --> 00:06:28.156
Take out the puri and
similarly fry all the puri

00:06:31.125 --> 00:06:33.469
Keep th gas medium

00:06:46.945 --> 00:06:50.250
Similarly make all the puri

00:06:50.758 --> 00:06:53.688
Mixed Urad Dal Puri is ready

00:06:53.688 --> 00:06:56.227
These are very crispy

00:06:56.265 --> 00:07:05.288
You can serve it with aloo sabzi, pumpkin
sabzi and raita in lunch or dinner

00:07:05.484 --> 00:07:08.531
Thanks for watching Urad Dal Puri

